              "name": "NoSQLInjection",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "User-supplied userName passed directly to MongoDB query without sanitization"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "In getUserByUserName and validateLogin, the userName from req.body is passed directly into MongoDB findOne queries without type checking or sanitization. An attacker can submit {\"userName\": {\"$gt\": \"\"}} as a JSON body to bypass authentication or enumerate users. Express body-parser with JSON content-type allows object injection into string fields."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Injection_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["A03:2021-Injection", "CWE-943"]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "USER-ENUMERATION",
              "name": "UserEnumeration",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Signup endpoint reveals whether a username already exists"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "When a duplicate userName is submitted, the signup handler returns 'User name already in use. Please choose another'. This allows attackers to enumerate valid usernames. Combined with the login page's distinct error messages for invalid username vs invalid password (A2-2), this provides a complete user enumeration oracle."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Authentication_Cheat_Sheet.html#authentication-responses",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["A07:2021-Identification-and-Authentication-Failures", "CWE-204"]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "MASS-ASSIGNMENT",
              "name": "MassAssignment",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "User object constructed from request body fields without allowlist enforcement"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The handleSignup destructures specific fields from req.body, but if additional properties were spread or the DAO accepted extra fields, an attacker could inject isAdmin or other privilege-escalating fields. While destructuring provides partial protection, the addUser DAO function should enforce an explicit schema. MongoDB's schemaless nature amplifies this risk."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Mass_Assignment_Cheat_Sheet.html",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["A04:2021-Insecure-Design", "CWE-915"]
              }
            },
            {
