                "text": "No rate limiting on signup endpoint"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The POST /signup endpoint has no rate limiting, allowing automated mass account creation. An attacker can script bulk registrations to pollute the user database, consume resources, or use the accounts for further attacks."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Denial_of_Service_Cheat_Sheet.html",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["A04:2021-Insecure-Design", "CWE-770"]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "BROKEN-AUTH-SESSION-LOGIN",
              "name": "SessionFixation",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Login handler does not regenerate session ID"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The handleLoginRequest sets req.session.userId without calling req.session.regenerate(). The comment in the code explicitly documents this vulnerability. An attacker who obtains a session ID before login can hijack the authenticated session. Note: the signup handler correctly calls regenerate(), but the login handler does not."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Session_Management_Cheat_Sheet.html#renew-the-session-id-after-any-privilege-level-change",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["A07:2021-Identification-and-Authentication-Failures", "CWE-384"]
              }
            }
          ]
